Get Data Sets

getDatasets.Rd

getDataSets returns a list containing datasets that have been specified by index according to the output of showDatasets.

getDatasets(x)

Arguments

x

A numeric vector containing the indexes of the datasets to be loaded.

Value

A list of TreeSummarizedExperiments.

See also

showDatasets

Examples


library(MicrobiomeBenchmarkData)
datasets <- getDatasets(x = c(1,3))
